How would you briefly define a recursive function?
# recursion is the idea that a function calls itself.

What is the point of recursion? Is it more efficient than using a plain loop?
# Recursion is considered both a fundamental precept of computer science and a litmus test that separates the decent programmers from the terrible ones.

What are the 2 essential parts in a recursive function?
# base case and recursive case
Why is “stack overflow” relevant to a recursive problem?
# In recursive implementations of D&C algorithms, one must make sure that there is sufficient memory allocated for the recursion stack, otherwise, the execution may fail because of stack overflow.
